== 預測 ==
在第23太陽週期結束和第24太陽週期開始之間的極小值之前，有兩種理論預測了第24太陽週期的強度。一個陣營假設太陽保持長期記憶(第24太陽週期將是活躍的)，而另一個陣營則斷言它是短期記憶(寧靜的)。在2006年之前，這兩者的差異很大，少數研究人員預測這是"100年來最寧靜的太陽週期" <ref>{{cite web | last=Svalgaard | first=Leif | url=http://www.leif.org/research/Cycle%2024%20Smallest%20100%20years.pdf | title=Sunspot cycle 24: Smallest cycle in 100 years? | publisher=GEOPHYSICAL RESEARCH LETTERS, VOL. 32, L01104, doi:10.1029/2004GL021664, 2005 | access-date=2021-03-06 | archive-date=2014-03-27 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140327134836/http://www.leif.org/research/Cycle%2024%20Smallest%20100%20years.pdf | dead-url=no }}</ref>。 另一組研究人員，包括NASA的一名研究員，預測它"看起來將是自近400年前開始紀錄以來最活躍的週期之一<ref>{{cite web | last=Hathaway | first=David | title=Scientists Predict Big Solar Cycle | publisher=NASA | url=https://science.nasa.gov/science-news/science-at-nasa/2006/21dec_cycle24/ | date=December 21, 2006 | access-date=2021-03-06 | archive-date=2021-01-30 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210130063804/https://science.nasa.gov/science-news/science-at-nasa/2006/21dec_cycle24/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>。"  

預示第24太陽週期開始的高緯度黑子出現的延遲，使得"活躍週期"的研究者們向下修正了他們的預測。到2007年，人們的共識以5:4的比例，傾向於一個叫寧靜的週期<ref>{{cite web|title=Consensus Statement of the Solar Cycle 24 Prediction Panel |url=http://www.swpc.noaa.gov/SolarCycle/SC24/Statement_01.html |publisher=NOAA |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120130050556/http://www.swpc.noaa.gov/SolarCycle/SC24/Statement_01.html |archive-date=January 30, 2012 }}</ref>。到了2012年，因為已經是太陽極小期後的3年，共識是一個寧靜的週期。

在2009年5月，[[美國國家海洋暨大氣總署|美國國家海洋暨大氣總署]]{{link-en|太空天氣預報中心| Space Weather Prediction Center}}的第24太陽週期預測小組預測，這個週期在2013年5月達到黑子相對數90的峰值<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.swpc.noaa.gov/SolarCycle/|title=Solar Cycle Progression|date=8 May 2009|publisher=National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration|access-date=2010-09-23|archive-date=2012-06-04|archive-url=https://archive.today/20120604110852/http://www.swpc.noaa.gov/SolarCycle/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。在2012年5月，NASA的專家大衛·海瑟薇（davidhathaway）預測，在2013年春季將出現一個峰值，黑子相對數大約是60 <ref>{{cite web| title = Climate Change Sanity| date = 9 January 2013| url = http://cbdakota.wordpress.com/2013/01/09/nasa-revises-cycle-24-sunspot-prediction/#more-4996| access-date = 2021-03-06| archive-date = 2020-04-06| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200406011747/https://cbdakota.wordpress.com/2013/01/09/nasa-revises-cycle-24-sunspot-prediction/#more-4996| dead-url = no}}</ref>。

NASA資助並且使用了肯·沙頓(Ken Schatten)的理論模型<ref>{{cite web |title = Fair space weather for solar cycle 24 |publisher = GEOPHYSICAL RESEARCH LETTERS, VOL. 32, L21106, doi:10.1029/2005GL024363 |date = 2005 |url = http://192.211.16.13/z/zita/research/07dynamo/articles/Schatten2005GRL.pdf |access-date = 2015-08-27 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160121131245/http://192.211.16.13/z/zita/research/07dynamo/articles/Schatten2005GRL.pdf |archive-date = 2016-01-21 |url-status = dead }}</ref>，其中利用了太陽發電機模型，準確地預測了極小期的低值。這個方法利用太陽極小期的磁場強度與太陽極大期黑子數的相關關係，準確地預測了最近三個太陽活動周期的峰值太陽通量。沙頓的預測早在太陽極小期，也就是極大期的5-6年前就準確地提出了。

== 結果 ==
2013年初，經過幾個月的平靜之後，很明顯在2011年的活躍並不是廣泛預測的2012年末至2013年初[[太陽閃焰|太陽閃焰]]高峰和其它活動的前奏或序曲。這一出乎意料之外的活躍階段，促使一些科學家提出了雙峰的太陽活動極大期。第一個峰值在2011年達到99，第二個峰值在2014年達到101<ref>{{cite web|title = Solar Cycle Progression {{!}} NOAA NWS Space Weather Prediction Center|url = http://www.swpc.noaa.gov/products/solar-cycle-progression|website = www.swpc.noaa.gov|accessdate = 2015-07-06|archive-date = 2021-04-23|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210423034150/https://www.swpc.noaa.gov/products/solar-cycle-progression|dead-url = no}}</ref>。

== 投機 ==
[[File:2008_breach_of_Earth's_magnetic_shield.jpg|thumb]]

根據[[NASA|NASA]]的資料，在[[地球磁場|地球磁場]]比預期微弱的某些地區，在第24太陽週期的[[磁暴|磁暴]]強度可能會升高；此一事實是[[西彌斯衛星|西密斯衛星]]發現的<ref name='NASA 2008-12-16'>{{Cite news | title = Giant Breach in Earth's Magnetic Field Discovered | date = 2008-12-16 | url = https://science.nasa.gov/science-news/science-at-nasa/2008/16dec_giantbreach/ | work = NASA | accessdate = 2010-05-29 | archive-date = 2021-02-12 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210212003434/http://science.nasa.gov/science-news/science-at-NASA/2008/16dec_giantbreach/ | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name='Phillips 2010-06-14'>{{Cite news | first = Tony | last = Phillips | title = As the Sun Awakens, NASA Keeps a Wary Eye on Space Weather | date = 2010-06-14 | url = https://science.nasa.gov/science-news/science-at-nasa/2010/04jun_swef/ | work = Science@NASA | accessdate = 2010-06-15 | archive-date = 2021-03-20 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210320221857/https://science.nasa.gov/science-news/science-at-nasa/2010/04jun_swef | dead-url = no }}</ref>。預計穿透地球磁場的粒子數量會增加20倍<ref name='Thompson 2008-12-16'>{{Cite news | first = Andrea | last = Thompson | title = Leaks Found in Earth's Protective Magnetic Field | date = 2008-12-16 | url = http://www.space.com/scienceastronomy/081216-agu-solar-storm-shield-break.html | work = SPACE.com | accessdate = 2010-06-02 | quote = As it orbited Earth, THEMIS's five spacecraft were able to estimate the thickness of the band of solar particles coming when the fields were aligned — it turned out to be about 20 times the number that got in when the fields were anti-aligned. | archive-date = 2010-12-24 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20101224060008/http://www.space.com/scienceastronomy/081216-agu-solar-storm-shield-break.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>。關於它對地球的潛在影響，已經成為第24太陽週期各種各樣假設和評論的主題。

雖然天文物理學家[[加來道雄|加來道雄]]認為第24太陽週期的下一個極大值不一定會產生異常的地磁活動，但利用媒體對[[2012現象|2012現象]]的關注，提請人們注意需要制定戰略，應對此類事件可能造成的地面損害。他主張各國政府應確保電力基礎設施的完整性，以防止類似[[1859年太陽風暴|1859年太陽風暴]]造成的破壞再次發生<ref name='Kaku 2010-03-31'>{{Cite news | first = Michio | last = Kaku | title = A Possible Solar Storm in 2012? | date = 2010-03-31 | publisher = [[Big_Think|Big Think]] | url = http://bigthink.com/ideas/19371 | work = Dr. Kaku's Universe | accessdate = 2010-06-04 | quote = Communication systems and power systems worldwide could be wiped out for months at a time. Something this large would cause not just a localized but rather a continent-wide power outage. | archive-date = 2011-08-07 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110807095236/http://bigthink.com/ideas/19371 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

因為沒有以預期的慣例產生太陽黑子，當前的太陽活動周期是現時研究的主題。太陽黑子並沒有在最後的極小值(在2008年)之後立即出現，遲至2009年末才開始出現，而且出現率明顯地低於預期<ref name='New Scientist 14th June 2010'>{{Cite news | first = Stuart | last = Clark | title = What's wrong with the Sun? | date = 2010-03-31 | url = https://www.newscientist.com/article/mg20627640.800-whats-wrong-with-the-sun.html?page=1 | work = New Scientist | issue = 2764 | accessdate = 2021-03-07 | archive-date = 2012-10-21 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20121021014341/http://www.newscientist.com/article/mg20627640.800-whats-wrong-with-the-sun.html?page=1 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

在2012年4月19日，[[日本國家天文台|日本國家天文台]]預測太陽磁場將呈現[[四極子|四極]]構型<ref name="Hinode 2012/4/19">{{Cite news | title = Polar Field Reversal as observed with Hinode | date = 2012-04-19 | url = http://hinode.nao.ac.jp/news/120419PressRelease/index_e.shtml | work = NAOJ | access-date = 2012-06-21 | url-status = dead | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20120701095458/http://hinode.nao.ac.jp/news/120419PressRelease/index_e.shtml | archive-date = 2012-07-01 }}</ref>。

在2012這一整年，NASA發布新聞駁斥[[2012年現象|2012年現象]]和所謂的[[2012年現象|馬雅預言]]，將它們與太陽活動和[[太空天氣|太空天氣]]脫鉤<ref>{{Cite news | title = 12-21-2012 Just Another Day | date = 2012-07-03 | url = http://www.nasa.gov/multimedia/podcasting/jpl-asteroid20120307.html | work = NASA | accessdate = 2013-05-18 | archive-date = 2020-11-11 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201111193338/http://www.nasa.gov/multimedia/podcasting/jpl-asteroid20120307.html | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | title = Beyond 2012: Why the World Didn't End | date = 2012-12-22 | url = http://www.nasa.gov/topics/earth/features/2012.html | work = NASA | accessdate = 2013-05-18 | archive-date = 2011-02-22 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110222054800/http://www.nasa.gov/topics/earth/features/2012.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

